---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service | Still">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="pt-32 min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <section class="py-24 bg-surface flex-grow">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <header class="mb-16">
          <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-display text-primary leading-tight mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
          <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-on-surface-variant opacity-70">Last Updated: May 2026</p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-on-surface-variant space-y-12">
          
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-primary mb-4 border-b border-outline-variant pb-2">1. The Commission Model</h2>
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Still Studio provides bespoke digital design and development services. Each project is treated as a singular commission, defined by the specific scope, timeline, and architectural requirements outlined in your individual proposal. By initiating a commission, you agree to these terms in full.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-primary mb-4 border-b border-outline-variant pb-2">2. Payment Terms & Investment</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">To maintain our standard of singular design, the following payment structure applies:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Commencement Fee:</strong> A non-refundable fee of 50% is required to secure your place in our studio calendar.</li>
              <li><strong>Final Investment:</strong> The remaining balance is due prior to the "Launch" phase of your digital portal.</li>
              <li><strong>Custom Quotes:</strong> All prices are tailored based on guest scale and concierge requirements.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-primary mb-4 border-b border-outline-variant pb-2">3. Intellectual Property & Licensing</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">We protect the "Digital Heirloom" quality of our work through specific IP protections:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Studio Ownership:</strong> Still Studio retains all ownership of underlying source code, proprietary frameworks, and architectural design elements.</li>
              <li><strong>Client License:</strong> Upon final payment, the client is granted an exclusive, non-transferable license to use the final portal for the duration of their specific event cycle.</li>
              <li><strong>Restraints:</strong> Designs may not be reproduced, resold, or repurposed without express written consent from the studio.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-primary mb-4 border-b border-outline-variant pb-2">4. Cancellations & Revisions</h2>
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Cancellations must be submitted in writing. While the commencement fee is non-refundable, we offer a structured revision process of two comprehensive cycles during the design phase. Significant structural changes requested post-launch may incur additional "Concierge Support" fees.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-display text-primary mb-4 border-b border-outline-variant pb-2">5. Governing Law</h2>
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              These terms are governed by the laws of your designated jurisdiction. Any disputes arising from a commission with Still Studio shall be resolved exclusively within the courts of said jurisdiction.
            </p>
          </section>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>